		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Enabling NMIs from a disabled state ($2000.7 goes from 0-&gt;1) when $2002.7 is set triggers an NMI.<br /><br />Just like $2002.7 going from 0-&gt;1 when $2000.7 triggers one.<br /><br />I don't know if any games rely on this behavior.</div>
<br />Bases Loaded II does.  If you don't implement this behavior, it'll glitch after a pitch is thrown.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.nemulator.com/images/bl2_glitch.jpg" alt="Image" />
